description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secondment (10 month) - Team Leader Hastings ATS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Mental Health Practitioner looking to take the next step in your career?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to gain an accredited leadership qualification while being part of a supportive leadership team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a practitioner with significant experience of working in mental health services who is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compassionate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well organised&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Motivated to provide the best service for patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During your secondment you will lead part of the multidisciplinary Assessment and Treatment Service to deliver services to clients with severe and enduring mental health challenges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported by the Service Manager, your Team Leader colleague and clinical leads to learn about:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Service organisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would really like to speak to you ahead of your application so please give one of the following people a call: Becky Marshall, Service Manager on 07471034200&lt;/p&gt;
